# Talos EPP — baseline hash-signature database
# Format:  <sha256-hex>  <Family.Name>
# Lines starting with '#' are comments; blank lines are ignored.
#
# This is the STATIC seed set shipped with the binary.  It contains only
# confirmed-malicious SHA-256 hashes from widely-cited public advisories.
# All entries have been cross-referenced against at least two public sources
# (US-CERT/CISA advisories, Cisco Talos blog, Kaspersky SecureList, ESET
# Threat Intelligence, Mandiant/Crowdstrike public reports).
#
# The live threat-intelligence feed (feeds.rs) supplements this set
# automatically with the abuse.ch MalwareBazaar hash feed, Feodo C2 hashes,
# and Spamhaus DROP.  Operators grow the database further via:
#   talos scan <path> --json > scan.log && talos ingest scan.log
#
# Only CONFIRMED-MALICIOUS samples belong here — a hash signature is an
# exact-match fingerprint, permanent until manually removed.  Generalised
# detections (packer families, TTPs) belong in signatures/yara/ instead.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# EICAR standard anti-malware test file (harmless industry test vector).
# Source: https://www.eicar.org/download-anti-malware-testfile/
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
275a021bbfb6489e54d471899f7db9d1663fc695ec2fe2a2c4538aabf651fd0f  Eicar.Test.File

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# WannaCry / WannaCrypt ransomware worm (May 2017)
# Propagation vector: EternalBlue (MS17-010) + DoublePulsar backdoor.
# Sources: US-CERT TA17-132A; NCSC MAR-10085923; Cisco Talos 2017-05-12
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# mssecsvc.exe — primary worm/service binary responsible for propagation
ed01ebfbc9eb5bbea545af4d01bf5f1071661840480439c6e5babe8e080e41aa  Ransom.WannaCry
# WannaCry dropper (variant distributed via phishing before worm phase)
9b60c622546dc45cca64df935b71c26dcf4886d6fa811944dbc4e23db9335640  Ransom.WannaCry
# Additional confirmed sample from Cisco Talos analysis
24d004a104d4d54034dbcffc2a4b19a11f39008a575aa614ea04703480b1022c  Ransom.WannaCry

